[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.example.TikaAppUnpackerFuzzer.parseOne[0m[1m([0mTikaAppUnpackerFuzzer.jav[1;92ma:74[0m[1m)[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                 at                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.example.TikaAppUnpackerFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1m([0mTikaAppUnpackerFuzzer.jav[1;92ma:54[0m[1m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         DEDUP_TOKEN: ea76e639355e804b                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         == libFuzzer crashing input ==                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         A critical security vulnerability has been detected during fuzzing of Apache Tika's [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         unpacking functionality. The issue is a file path traversal vulnerability [1m([0mCWE-[1;36m22[0m[1m)[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         that allows writing files outside of the intended directory through the use of path [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         traversal sequences [1m([0m[32m"../"[0m[1m)[0m in archive entry names. The vulnerability is triggered  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         when Tika processes embedded documents within package/archive files and attempts to [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         extract them to the filesystem.                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The fuzzing test has identified a file path traversal security issue in Apache      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Tika's command-line interface [1m([0mTikaCLI[1m)[0m when handling embedded document extraction. [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The vulnerability manifests when processing archive files that contain entries with [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         malicious path traversal sequences.                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         **Vulnerability Type:** File Path Traversal [1m([0mDirectory Traversal[1m)[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         **Key Observations:**                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. **Detection Point**: The Jazzer security instrumentation detected an attempt to  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         access the path                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[35m/tmp/expander-tmp7178632824994909312/output/q/r/s/t/../../[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m`, which [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         resolves outside the intended output directory due to the [32m"../"[0m sequences.          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. **Attack Vector**: The stack trace indicates that the traversal occurs during    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         the extraction of embedded documents from package files. The malicious path         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `q/r/s/t/..[35m/../[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m` demonstrates how an attacker could craft an        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         archive entry name to escape the designated extraction directory.                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. **Execution Flow**: The vulnerability is triggered through the following call    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         chain:                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Archive parsing begins with `[1;35mPackageParser.parse[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Entries are processed via `[1;35mPackageParser.parseEntries[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` and                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mPackageParser.parseEntry[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Embedded document extraction is handled by                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `TikaCLI$[1;35mFileEmbeddedDocumentExtractor.parseEmbedded[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - File output processing occurs at                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mFilePathTraversal.processFileOutputStartHook[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` where the violation is detected    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. **Affected Components**: The issue involves the interaction between:             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Archive/package parsing functionality [1m([0m`PackageParser`[1m)[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Embedded document extraction [1m([0m`FileEmbeddedDocumentExtractor`[1m)[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - File system output operations in the CLI module                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         **Areas for Investigation:**                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. **TikaCLI$FileEmbeddedDocumentExtractor** [1m([0mline [1;36m1111[0m[1m)[0m: Examine how file paths    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         are constructed when extracting embedded documents, particularly how entry names    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         from archives are used to determine output file paths.                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. **PackageParser** [1m([0mlines [1;36m259[0m-[1;36m481[0m[1m)[0m: Review how package entries are processed and  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         whether entry names are validated or sanitized before being used in file system     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         operations.                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. **Path Construction Logic**: Investigate where and how the output file paths are [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         determined, specifically looking at how the temporary directory path is combined    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         with entry names from archives.                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. **Input Validation**: Determine if there are any existing path validation or     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         sanitization mechanisms and why they failed to prevent this traversal attempt.      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m. **File Output Operations**: Examine all locations where files are created during [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         the extraction process to ensure comprehensive path validation is applied           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         consistently.                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The vulnerability represents a critical security risk as it could allow an attacker [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         to write files to arbitrary locations on the filesystem by crafting a malicious     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         archive file, potentially leading to code execution, data corruption, or privilege  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         escalation depending on the execution context.                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Initial Issue Log                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m<[0m[1;95missue[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== Java Exception: com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: [0m   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m110[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtika-example/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/example/ExtractEmbeddedFiles.jav[0m[1;92ma:85[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m94[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m85[0m[39m:                [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[95mmake[0m[39m sure to select only the file name [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnot any directory [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpaths[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m86[0m[39m:                [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[95mthat[0m[39m might be included in the name[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and make sure[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m87[0m[39m:                [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[95mto[0m[39m normalize the name[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m88[0m[39m:                name = [0m[1;35mname.replaceAll[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"\u0000"[0m[39m, [0m[32m" "[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m89[0m[39m:                int prefix = [0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.getPrefixLength[0m[1;39m([0m[39mname[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m90[0m[39m:                if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mprefix > [0m[1;36m-1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m91[0m[39m:                    name = [0m[1;35mname.substring[0m[1;39m([0m[39mprefix[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m92[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m93[0m[39m:                name = [0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[39mname[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m94[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtika-core/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/pipes/fetcher/fs/FileSystemFetcher.jav[0m[1;92ma:64[0m[39m-[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m82[0m                                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m64[0m[39m:    static boolean [0m[1;35misDescendant[0m[1;39m([0m[39mPath root, Path descendant[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m65[0m[39m:        return [0m[1;35mdescendant.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m66[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35m.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mroot.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m67[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m68[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m69[0m[39m:    @Override[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m70[0m[39m:    public InputStream [0m[1;35mfetch[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString fetchKey, Metadata metadata, ParseContext [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparseContext[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException, TikaException [0m[1;39m{[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m71[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mfetchKey.contains[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"\u0000"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m72[0m[39m:            throw new [0m[1;35mIllegalArgumentException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Path must not contain 'u0000'. "[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m73[0m[39m:                    [0m[32m"Please review the life decisions that led you to requesting[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"[0m[39m +[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m74[0m[39m:                    [0m[32m"a file name with this character in it."[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m75[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m76[0m[39m:        Path p = null;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m77[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbasePath != null[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m78[0m[39m:            p = [0m[1;35mbasePath.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfetchKey[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m79[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mp.toRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mbasePath.toRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m80[0m[39m:                throw new [0m[1;35mIllegalArgumentException[0m[1;39m([0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m81[0m[39m:                        [0m[32m"fetchKey must resolve to be a descendant of the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m'basePath'"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m82[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Analysis[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter analyzing the code snippets and the evaluation report, I've identified the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mroot cause and optimal fix strategy for this critical path traversal vulnerability.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Root Cause Analysis[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe vulnerability exists in `TikaCLI$[0m[1;35mFileEmbeddedDocumentExtractor.getOutputFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethod [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1128[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1169[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The issue occurs because:[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Insufficient Sanitization**: The code uses Apache Commons IO's [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m1141[0m[39m, but this method alone does NOT prevent [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectory traversal when combined with `new [0m[1;35mFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mparent, child[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` constructor.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Incorrect Fallback Logic**: `[0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is only called as a [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfallback when `[0m[1;35mnormalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` returns null [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m1144[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, not as the primary security [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmeasure.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Vulnerable Path Construction**: At line [0m[1;36m1160[0m[39m, `new [0m[1;35mFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mextractDir, [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnormalizedName[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` allows paths like [0m[32m"q/r/s/t/../../jazzer-traversal"[0m[39m to escape the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mintended extraction directory.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **No Path Validation**: There's no verification that the final resolved path [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstays within the `extractDir` boundary before file creation at line [0m[1;36m1111[0m[39m.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Existing Secure Patterns in Tika[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe codebase already contains THREE secure patterns that should be applied:[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Tika's [0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtika-core[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Explicitly designed to prevent [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpath traversal attacks like [0m[32m"../../../file.txt"[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **ExtractEmbeddedFiles Example** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtika-example[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Shows the correct usage: [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[39mname[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **FileSystemFetcher Pattern** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtika-core[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Validates final resolved paths using [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Primary Fix: Apply Filename Extraction Pattern[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mModify `TikaCLI$[0m[1;35mFileEmbeddedDocumentExtractor.getOutputFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to use the secure [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpattern already demonstrated in `ExtractEmbeddedFiles.java`:[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location**: `tika-app/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/cli/TikaCLI.java` lines [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1128[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1169[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Changes**:[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Line [0m[1;36m1141[0m[39m Modification**: Change from using only [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[39mname[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to using BOTH `[0m[1;35mgetName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mnormalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtogether:[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Current: `String normalizedName = [0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[39mname[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Fixed: `String normalizedName = [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mFilenameUtils.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[39mname[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   This ensures that:[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` first extracts ONLY the filename, stripping all [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectory components[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any path traversal sequences like [0m[32m"../"[0m[39m or [0m[32m"q/r/s/t/../.."[0m[39m are removed[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` then normalizes the resulting filename[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Maintain Existing Fallback Logic**: Lines [0m[1;36m1143[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1149[0m[39m already handle cases where[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnormalize returns null, so this logic remains unchanged and provides [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdefense-in-depth.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Line [0m[1;36m1163[0m[39m Consistency**: The existing code at line [0m[1;36m1163[0m[39m already uses [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` when handling duplicate files, which is correct. This [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchange makes the primary path consistent with this existing secure usage.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Secondary Fix: Add Path Validation [0m[1;39m([0m[39mDefense-in-Depth[0m[1;39m)[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAdd runtime validation after path construction to catch any edge cases:[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location**: After line [0m[1;36m1160[0m[39m in `[0m[1;35mgetOutputFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Changes**:[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAdd validation logic using the pattern from FileSystemFetcher:[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter: File outputFile = new [0m[1;35mFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mextractDir, normalizedName[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAdd:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtry [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    Path outputPath = [0m[1;35moutputFile.toPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    Path extractPath = [0m[1;35mextractDir.toPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35moutputPath.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[39mextractPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Security: Path traversal detected in: "[0m[39m + name[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mIOException e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m fails if file doesn't exist yet, fall back to absolute path [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcheck[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    Path outputPath = [0m[1;35moutputFile.toPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    Path extractPath = [0m[1;35mextractDir.toPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35moutputPath.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[39mextractPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Security: Path traversal detected in: "[0m[39m + name[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNote: This validation needs special handling because `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` requires the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfile to exist, but we're validating before creating the file. The fallback to [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mtoAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` handles this case.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Critical Implementation Notes[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Use Apache Commons IO's FilenameUtils**: The code already imports [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.commons.io.FilenameUtils` at line [0m[1;36m59[0m[39m. Continue using this for [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconsistency with the existing codebase.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Preserve Existing Functionality**: [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Keep the null byte removal [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m1140[0m[1;39m)[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Keep the prefix stripping [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1151[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1154[0m[1;39m)[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Keep the URL decoding [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1156[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1159[0m[1;39m)[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Keep the UUID prepending for existing files [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1162[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1167[0m[1;39m)[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Keep the extension handling [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1129[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1132[0m[1;39m)[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Keep the relationship ID prepending [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1134[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1137[0m[1;39m)[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Do NOT Modify**:[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - PackageParser entry processing [0m[1;39m([0m[39mit's not responsible for path validation[0m[1;39m)[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Harness or fuzzing code[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Test code[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The extractDir initialization or handling[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Imports**: No additional imports needed - all required utilities are already [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimported.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why This is Optimal[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Follows Existing Patterns**: The fix applies the same secure pattern already [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mused in `ExtractEmbeddedFiles.java` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m93[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which is provided as an example in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe Tika codebase.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Uses Existing Utilities**: Leverages `[0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` which is [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexplicitly documented [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m88[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m90[0m[39m in tika-core FilenameUtils[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m as preventing [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"../../../my_ppt.ppt"[0m[39m attacks.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Minimal Code Changes**: The primary fix requires changing only ONE line [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[1;36m1141[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, reducing the risk of introducing new bugs.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Defense-in-Depth**: Combining filename extraction with runtime path validation[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprovides multiple layers of security.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **No Breaking Changes**: [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing tests will continue to work [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthey expect files under extractDir[0m[1;39m)[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Legitimate filenames are preserved[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Only malicious path traversal sequences are blocked[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### How It Addresses the Issue[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Prevents Path Traversal**: `[0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` strips all directory [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomponents, so [0m[32m"q/r/s/t/../../jazzer-traversal"[0m[39m becomes just [0m[32m"jazzer-traversal"[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Handles Edge Cases**: The fallback logic [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1143[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1149[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m handles cases where[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mgetName returns null or empty string[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Runtime Validation**: The secondary fix validates that even if getName somehow[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallows a traversal [0m[1;39m([0m[39medge case[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the runtime check catches it[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Preserves Subdirectories**: If legitimate subdirectories are needed [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthough [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mgetName prevents this[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, they can be recreated based on EMBEDDED_RELATIONSHIP_ID or [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mother metadata, not from untrusted entry names[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Potential Side Effects and Mitigation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Flattened Directory Structure**: Using `[0m[1;35mgetName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` will flatten the directory [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstructure since all directory components are removed from entry names.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: This is the CORRECT behavior for security. If directory [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstructure preservation is needed, it should be based on trusted metadata [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlike [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mEMBEDDED_RELATIONSHIP_ID[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m not untrusted entry names.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The existing code at lines [0m[1;36m1134[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1137[0m[39m already prepends [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mEMBEDDED_RELATIONSHIP_ID, which can provide some structure.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Filename Collisions**: More files may have the same name after stripping [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectory components.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: The existing UUID prepending logic [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1162[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1167[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m already [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhandles this.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Lost Context**: Some archive entries may have meaningful directory structure.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: The directory path information is preserved in metadata and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcan be logged or used in other ways, just not for file system path construction.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Reference to Similar Solutions[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **ExtractEmbeddedFiles.java** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m93[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Already demonstrates the correct [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpattern[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **FileSystemFetcher.java** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m78[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m82[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Shows the path validation pattern[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **[0m[1;35mFSUtil.resolveRelative[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m197[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m203[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Shows rejection of problematic [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpaths[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAll three patterns are from the official Apache Tika codebase, confirming this is [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe intended security approach.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.example.TikaAppUnpackerFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1m([0mTikaAppUnpackerFuzzer.jav[1;92ma:54[0m[1m)[0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         == libFuzzer crashing input ==                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The initial issue is a security vulnerability [1m([0mpath traversal attack[1m)[0m detected by a [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         fuzzer while extracting embedded documents from archive files processed by Apache   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Tika. The fuzzer identified that file paths like                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"/tmp/expander-tmp7178632824994909312/output/q/r/s/t/../../jazzer-traversal"[0m could  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         be used to write files outside the intended extraction directory. A patch was       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         attempted to prevent this vulnerability by normalizing file paths and validating    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         that output files remain within the extraction directory. However, the patch failed [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         to compile due to uncaught IOException errors that were not properly handled in the [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         method signature.                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ### Initial Issue                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The fuzzer detected a critical security vulnerability classified as [32m"File path [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mtraversal"[0m when processing archive files. The stack trace shows:                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. The vulnerability is triggered in                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `TikaCLI$[1;35mFileEmbeddedDocumentExtractor.parseEmbedded[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` at line [1;36m1111[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. The issue occurs during the extraction of embedded documents from                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         package/archive files                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. The problematic path is                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"/tmp/expander-tmp7178632824994909312/output/q/r/s/t/../../jazzer-traversal"[0m, which [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         demonstrates a classic path traversal attack pattern using [32m"../"[0m sequences          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. The call chain shows the vulnerability manifests when:                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - `PackageParser` processes archive entries                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - `[1;35mFileEmbeddedDocumentExtractor.parseEmbedded[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` attempts to extract embedded   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         content                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The file path sanitizer [1m([0m`[1;35mFilePathTraversal.check[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`[1m)[0m detects the traversal    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         attempt                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The security scanner specifically flags this as a [32m"FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical"[0m,    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         indicating that an attacker could potentially write files outside the intended      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         extraction directory.                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ### Patch Attempt                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The patch modifies the `TikaCLI.java` file, specifically the                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `FileEmbeddedDocumentExtractor` class's file handling logic. The changes include:   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. **Initial Path Normalization Enhancement [1m([0mline [1;36m1141[0m-[1;36m1142[0m[1m)[0m**:                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Changed from: `String normalizedName = [1;35mFilenameUtils.normalize[0m[1m([0mname[1m)[0m;`         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Changed to: `String normalizedName =                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mFilenameUtils.normalize[0m[1m([0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.getName[0m[1m([0mname[1m)[0m[1m)[0m;`                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The modification extracts only the filename using `[1;35mFilenameUtils.getName[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         before normalization, which removes any directory path components                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. **Path Traversal Validation [1m([0mlines [1;36m1163[0m-[1;36m1176[0m[1m)[0m**:                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Added a try-catch block after the `outputFile` is created                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Converts both `outputFile` and `extractDir` to absolute, normalized paths      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Uses `[1;35mPath.startsWith[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` to verify that the output path is within the          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         extraction directory                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Throws an IOException with a security message if traversal is detected:        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"Security: Path traversal attempt detected in entry name: "[0m + name                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Handles SecurityException by wrapping it in an IOException                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ### Compilation Errors                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The patch failed to compile with two specific errors at lines [1;36m1174[0m and [1;36m1176[0m:        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ```                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m[[0mERROR[1m][0m unreported exception java.io.IOException; must be caught or declared to be  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         thrown                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ```                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         These errors occur because:                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. The new code throws IOException [1m([0mboth explicitly at line [1;36m1174[0m and when           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         re-throwing at line [1;36m1176[0m[1m)[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. The method containing this code [1m([0m`[1;35mparseEmbedded[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`[1m)[0m does not declare IOException [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         in its throws clause                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. The IOException is not caught within the method                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The compilation errors indicate that the method signature needs to be updated to    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         include IOException, or the exception handling logic needs to be restructured.      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ### Areas for Further Investigation                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         To fully understand and properly fix this vulnerability, the following areas should [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         be investigated:                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. **Method Signature of `[1;35mparseEmbedded[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`**: Examine the current method signature  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         to understand what exceptions it declares and whether adding IOException would      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         break the contract with any interfaces or parent classes.                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. **EmbeddedDocumentExtractor Interface**: Check if `[1;35mparseEmbedded[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` implements   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         an interface method that constrains what exceptions can be thrown.                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. **Existing Error Handling**: Review how errors are currently handled in the      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `FileEmbeddedDocumentExtractor` class around lines [1;36m1100[0m-[1;36m1200[0m to ensure consistency  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         with the codebase's error handling patterns.                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. **File Path Handling Flow**: Trace the complete flow from when an archive entry  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         name is received through to file creation to identify all points where path         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         manipulation occurs [1m([0mlines [1;36m1138[0m-[1;36m1180[0m based on the patch context[1m)[0m.                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m. **FilenameUtils Behavior**: Understand the behavior of                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mFilenameUtils.normalize[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` and `[1;35mFilenameUtils.getName[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` to ensure the combination [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         provides adequate protection.                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m. **Upstream Callers**: Investigate callers of `[1;35mparseEmbedded[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` to determine if   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         they expect and can handle IOException, or if a different exception type would be   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         more appropriate.                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m78[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m79[0m[39m:     * This is a duplication of the algorithm and functionality[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m80[0m[39m:     * available in commons io FilenameUtils.  If Java's File were[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m81[0m[39m:     * able handle Windows file paths correctly in linux,[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m82[0m[39m:     * we wouldn't need this.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m83[0m[39m:     * <p>[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m84[0m[39m:     * The goal of this is to get a filename from a path.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m85[0m[39m:     * The package parsers and some other embedded doc[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m86[0m[39m:     * extractors could put anything into TikaCoreProperties.RESOURCE_NAME_KEY.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m87[0m[39m:     * <p>[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m88[0m[39m:     * If a careless client used that filename as if it were a[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m89[0m[39m:     * filename and not a path when writing embedded files,[0m                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1109[0m[39m:            [0m[1;35mSystem.out.println[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Extracting '"[0m[39m + name + [0m[32m"' [0m[32m([0m[32m"[0m[39m + contentType + [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"[0m[32m)[0m[32m to "[0m[39m + outputFile[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
