[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1111[0m[39m:            try [0m[1;39m([0m[39mFileOutputStream os = new [0m[1;35mFileOutputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[39moutputFile[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1112[0m[39m:                if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35membeddedStreamTranslator.shouldTranslate[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtis, metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1113[0m[39m:                    try [0m[1;39m([0m[39mInputStream translated = [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35membeddedStreamTranslator.translate[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtis, metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1114[0m[39m:                        [0m[1;35mIOUtils.copy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtranslated, os[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1115[0m[39m:                    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1116[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1117[0m[39m:                    [0m[1;35mIOUtils.copy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtis, os[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1118[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1119[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mException e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1120[0m[39m:                [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1121[0m[39m:                [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m being a CLI program messages should go to the stderr too[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1122[0m[39m:                [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1123[0m[39m:                String msg = [0m[1;35mString.format[0m[1;39m([0m[39mLocale.ROOT, [0m[32m"Ignoring unexpected [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mexception trying to save embedded file %s [0m[32m([0m[32m%s[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, name, [0m[1;35me.getMessage[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1124[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35mLOG.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmsg, e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Analysis of the Issue[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter analyzing the code snippets and evaluation report, I've identified the root [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcause of both the security vulnerability and the compilation errors:[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Security Vulnerability**: The path traversal attack occurs because:[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Line [0m[1;36m1141[0m[39m in `[0m[1;35mgetOutputFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` applies `[0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[39mname[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfull path including directory components[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This allows malicious paths like [0m[32m"q/r/s/t/../../jazzer-traversal"[0m[39m to partially[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mescape through normalization[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The `[0m[1;35mgetName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` fallback [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m1144[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m only applies when [0m[1;35mnormalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m returns [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnull[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The best practice [0m[1;39m([0m[39mshown in ExtractEmbeddedFiles.java[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is to apply `[0m[1;35mgetName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBEFORE `[0m[1;35mnormalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Compilation Errors**: The failed patch attempted to throw IOException inside [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe `[0m[1;35mgetOutputFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1174[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m1176[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but this method doesn't declare [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`throws IOException` in its signature [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m1128[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The correct location for [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidation is in the `[0m[1;35mparseEmbedded[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method which already declares `throws [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIOException` at line [0m[1;36m1091[0m[39m.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Core Insights from Code Analysis[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Interface Contract**: The `EmbeddedDocumentExtractor` interface [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtika-core[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeclares `[0m[1;35mparseEmbedded[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` with `throws SAXException, IOException`, so throwing [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIOException is allowed[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Proven Pattern**: FileSystemFetcher uses [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mPath.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` for path validation[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Best Practice**: ExtractEmbeddedFiles.java shows the correct order: [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[39mname[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Validation Timing**: Must validate AFTER `[0m[1;35mgetOutputFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` returns but BEFORE [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FileOutputStream` is created[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fix requires **two modifications** to [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tika-app/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/cli/TikaCLI.java`:[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Change [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: Improve Filename Sanitization in `[0m[1;35mgetOutputFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` Method[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location**: Line [0m[1;36m1141[0m[39m in the `[0m[1;35mgetOutputFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Modification**: Change the normalization order to extract the filename BEFORE [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnormalizing:[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Current [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvulnerable[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mString normalizedName = [0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[39mname[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Fixed [0m[1;39m([0m[39msecure[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mString normalizedName = [0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[39mname[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Rationale**:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` extracts only the filename, stripping ALL directory [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpath components [0m[1;39m([0m[39mhandles [0m[32m"/"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"\", and "[0m[39m:" separators[0m[1;39m)[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This prevents paths like [0m[32m"subdir/../../../evil.txt"[0m[39m or [0m[32m"q/r/s/t/../../traversal"[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfrom preserving any directory traversal[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Then `[0m[1;35mnormalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` sanitizes the remaining filename for reserved characters[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This matches the proven pattern in ExtractEmbeddedFiles.java [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m93[0m[1;39m)[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This is defense-in-depth layer [0m[1;36m1[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Change [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: Add Path Traversal Validation in `[0m[1;35mparseEmbedded[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` Method[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location**: After line [0m[1;36m1100[0m[39m in the `[0m[1;35mparseEmbedded[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method, immediately after [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mgetOutputFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` returns but before the parent directory check[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Modification**: Insert validation code to verify the output file remains within [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe extraction directory:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moutputFile = [0m[1;35mgetOutputFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mname, metadata, contentType[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Validate that the resolved output path stays within the extraction directory[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m This prevents path traversal attacks as a defense-in-depth measure[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtry [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    Path outputPath = [0m[1;35moutputFile.toPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    Path extractPath = [0m[1;35mextractDir.toPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35moutputPath.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[39mextractPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Security: attempted path traversal in embedded file [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mname: "[0m[39m + name[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mIOException e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Re-throw IOException [0m[1;39m([0m[39mincluding our security exception from above[0m[1;39m)[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    throw e;[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSecurityException e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Wrap SecurityException as IOException for consistent error handling[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Security: path validation failed for embedded file: "[0m[39m + [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mname, e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFile parent = [0m[1;35moutputFile.getParentFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Rationale**:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Uses the Path API's `[0m[1;35mtoAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` which properly handles [0m[32m".."[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msegments without requiring the file to exist[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The `[0m[1;35mstartsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method reliably checks if outputPath is within extractPath[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Follows the pattern from FileSystemFetcher [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m67[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m79[0m[1;39m)[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Throws IOException in a method that already declares it [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m1091[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, avoiding [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompilation errors[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Catches and re-throws IOException to preserve security exceptions[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Catches SecurityException and wraps it as IOException for consistency[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This is defense-in-depth layer [0m[1;36m2[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Validation occurs at the correct time: after path construction but before any [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfile system operations[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Why This Approach is Optimal[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Defense-in-Depth**: Two layers of protection ensure security even if one layer[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhas edge cases[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Compilation Safety**: IOException is thrown only in methods that declare it[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Proven Patterns**: Uses established patterns from FileSystemFetcher and [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mExtractEmbeddedFiles[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Minimal Changes**: Only modifies the vulnerable code paths without breaking [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexisting functionality[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Cross-Platform**: Path API handles Windows and Unix paths correctly[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Backward Compatible**: Doesn't change method signatures or external APIs[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. **Test Friendly**: Existing tests will continue to work for legitimate files; [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmalicious paths will be rejected[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Preserved Logic[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fallback logic [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1143[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1149[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m remains intact for when [0m[1;35mgetName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m returns [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mempty[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The UUID prepending for duplicate files [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1162[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1167[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is unaffected[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The parent directory creation [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1103[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1108[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m still works but only for [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidated paths[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The exception handling in the try-catch block [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1119[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1125[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m continues to [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcatch file operation errors[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All other filename processing [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnull byte removal, prefix stripping, URL decoding[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremains unchanged[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Potential Side Effects and Mitigation[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Archives with legitimate nested directories**: Change [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m will flatten all [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectory structures from embedded file names. This is INTENTIONAL for security but[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrepresents a behavior change.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Mitigation: The original directory path information is still in the metadata [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mRESOURCE_NAME_KEY[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m for logging purposes[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The extraction still succeeds; files just go directly into extractDir instead [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof nested subdirectories[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Error messages for rejected paths**: Users will now see [0m[32m"Security: attempted [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mpath traversal"[0m[39m errors for malicious archives[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Mitigation: This is correct behavior - the error message clearly indicates why[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mextraction failed[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Performance**: Path validation adds minimal overhead [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath normalization and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstring comparison[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Mitigation: This is negligible compared to I/O operations[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Related Code That Should NOT Be Modified[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Do NOT modify PackageParser [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtika-parsers[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m - it correctly passes through archive [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentry names[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Do NOT modify the EmbeddedDocumentExtractor interface - it already supports [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIOException[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Do NOT modify the fuzzer harness - it's just triggering the vulnerability, not [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpart of the fix[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Do NOT modify test utilities in TikaCLITest - tests should validate the fix works[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcorrectly[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
